---
description: Spell, spellbook, schema, policy, and adapter guidance
globs:
  - "**/*.spell.json"
  - "**/spell.schema.json"
  - "**/spellbook.schema.json"
  - "**/spellbook.json"
  - "**/default.policy.json"
  - "**/*.openapi.yaml"
  - "**/*.openapi.yml"
  - "**/examples/*.json"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Spell examples should remain runnable and demonstrate a specific concept.
- Spellbooks should expose clear entrypoints and keep paths relative and portable.
- Schema changes must preserve backwards clarity or come with migration notes.
- Keep policy defaults conservative: risky writes should require approval.
- Adapters are demos, not security boundaries. Document assumptions clearly.
- If you add a new spell or spellbook field, update the matching schema, `README.md`, and at least one example.
